  "text": "The C# type inference and method overload resolution pipeline in dotnet/roslyn consists of several key components located in src/Compilers/CSharp/Portable/Binder/Semantics/:\n\n1. **OverloadResolution.cs** (sealed partial class): The central class coordinating method overload resolution. It contains three main public entry points:\n   - ObjectCreationOverloadResolution: Resolves constructor overloads for object creation\n   - MethodInvocationOverloadResolution: Resolves method call overloads\n   - PropertyOverloadResolution: Resolves property access overloads\n   \n   The BetterFunctionMember method (defined at lines 1951 and 1990) compares two candidate methods to determine which is a better match according to the C# specification, using ranking criteria like parameter specificity and conversion cost.\n\n2. **MethodTypeInference.cs**: Implements the generic type argument inference mechanism through the MethodTypeInferrer struct (line 91). The static entry point is the Infer method (line 166) which orchestrates a two-phase type inference process. MethodTypeInferrer performs the critical task of inferring generic type arguments for generic methods before overload resolution completes, by analyzing argument-to-parameter type relationships and collecting type bounds.\n\n3. **Conversions/Conversions.cs** (sealed class inheriting from ConversionsBase): Encapsulates C# conversion rules and rankings. This class is used throughout overload resolution to rank implicit conversions and determine conversion costs, which directly affects method selection when multiple overloads could apply.\n\n4. **BestTypeInferrer.cs** (static class): Provides type inference utilities specifically for array initialization expressions and conditional expressions. It infers the best common type from a set of expressions by analyzing type compatibility, handling nullable annotations and flow states.\n\n5. **OverloadResolutionResult.cs**: Stores the results of overload resolution, including the selected candidate, applicability assessments, and diagnostics about why candidates were rejected.\n\nThe type inference and overload resolution chain flows as follows: When a method group is encountered, MethodTypeInferrer.Infer is applied to each generic method to infer type arguments. Then OverloadResolution orchestrates the selection by comparing candidates using BetterFunctionMember, with the Conversions class ranking conversion costs to determine the best match. Finally, BestTypeInferrer handles special cases for array and conditional expression type inference."
}

